.DT
cast
$MUDNAME$ player help
cast

.SH Name
.SI 5
cast - Spell or ritual casting
.EI

.SH Syntax
.SI 5
cast <spell> [from <scroll>] [at|on <target|targets>]
     [using <components>] [with <argument>]
.EI

.SH Description
.SP 5 5
Cast is used when you want to activate a spell or ritual that you have learnt,
been taught or found in a scroll on your adventures.  You must use cast
followed by the spell you wish to cast followed by any information that is
appropriate to the spell.

Note that the name of the spell/ritual is case sensitive, and should be
typed exactly as you see it with the spells and rituals commands.
.EP

.SH Example
.SI 5
> cast light
The world lights up as you cast your spell.
> cast heal on shaydz
Shaydz looks like he really liked that.
> cast bees on shiannar using 3 dollops of honey
Shiannar looks really excited about the gift of honey.
.EI

.SH See also
.SI 5
spells, rituals
.EI
